history.text: If you haven't seen Jaws, you should. It's a movie about a great white shark attacking people in a resort town.
that does sound interesting, Who plays the main characters?
Also, do you know how long the movie is?
Roy Schneider is the main character, Chief Martin Brody. Robert Shaw, Richard Dreyfuss, and Lorraine Gary are also in it.
I don't know exactly how long it is.
How would you rate the movie itself, 1-10
Most people would rate it an 8 or 9, and I agree with that.
Thank you for the information, I think I will check it out!
If you have any kids, you probably don't want to let them watch it. It's kind of gory.
I will definitely keep that in mind, do you know when the movie came out?
1975. It's based on a 1974 novel.
Is there any other important information about the movie that I should know about?

The opening scene is pretty cool. A woman gets attacked at a beach party, and the chief of police says its a shark attack, but the mayor tells everyone it was a boating accident so that tourists don't leave. Then a professional shark hunter shows up. Very exciting.
Sounds like my type of movie. Again, thank you for the information.
No problem. I think it has a 97% on Rotten Tomatoes, so most everyone likes it.
Is there anything else we have to cover, or how do we finish this conversation?
Well, I'd love to tell you about the next scene, since I keep learning new information about the movie. There's another big death at the beach's fourth of july celebration.
Okay, what are some of the other big scenes in the movie?
Does the shark hunter eventually capture or kill the shark?

Well, apparently they catch a tiger shark and the mayor says the beaches are safe. Some people think it's the wrong shark, especially when they find a sunken ship with a big shark tooth. But the fourth of July plans go on anyway, and someone dies.
Not sure yet. But I know they hire him after the mayor's son goes into shock.

uid2response.feedback: Told too much detail on what happens during the movie, I prefer not to know some of the major details before watching an actual movie.
